.TH libvdfc 3 "20th July 2026" "version 1.0"

.SH NAME
libvdfc \- Valve Data Format Parser Library

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <vdfc/vdf.h>

.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fB libvdfc \fR library provides a small API for reading and parsing files
in Valve Data Format (VDF), the key-value format used by Steam configuration and
manifest files.

A typical usage reads a file into memory with \fBvdf_read_file\fR,
parses the buffer into a tree of \fBVDFNode\fR with \fBvdf_parse\fR
walks the tree with \fBvdf_get\fR and its typed variants like
\fBvdf_get_string\fR, \fBvdf_get_int\fR, \fBvdf_get_bool\fR.
And releases the tree with \fBvdf_free_node\fR.

The user can also choose to allocate and fill the tree into a buffer
with \fBvdf_dump_node\fR.

Each \fBVDFNode\fR is either a string value or an object holding child nodes;
the root node returned by \fB`vdf_parse`\fR owns all memory in the tree,
which is released in one call by \fBvdf_free_node\fR.

All functions that can fail return a \fB`VDFcode`\fR status;
see \fBlibvdfc_errors\fR(3) for the list of codes.

